  "texts": [
    "There are now a number of reliable and efficient solvers for such problems, including open-source ones like ECOS [DCB13], Clarabel [GC24], and SCS [OCPB16], and commercial solvers such as MOSEK [ApS20], GUROBI [Gur23], and CPLEX [Cpl09].",
    "A recent open-source solver for QPs is OSQP [SBG + 20].",
    "Domain-specific languages.",
    "Convex optimization is also now very accessible to practitioners, even those without a strong background in the mathematics or algorithms of convex optimization, thanks to high-level domain-specific languages (DSLs) for convex optimization, such as CVXPY [AVDB18, DB16], CVX [GB14], Convex.jl [UMZ + 14], CVXR [FNB17], and YALMIP [Lof04].",
    "These DSLs make it easy to specify complex, but convex, optimization problems in a natural, human readable way."
  ],
